[{"id":"VR134038","type":"longtextV2","stimulusHtml":"<div>\n<div class=\"stimulus_reference\">\n<p class=\"lead_in\">Use the following two images to answer all parts of the question that follows.</p>\n\n<div class=\"passage\">\n<div class=\"prose style:1\">\n<p class=\"passage_para\">a) Identify ONE way that <span class=\"formatted_text text_decoration:underline\">Image 1</span> illustrates an effect of Mongol rule in Eurasia.</p>\n\n<p class=\"passage_para\">b) Explain ONE likely purpose for the inclusion of <span class=\"formatted_text text_decoration:underline\">Image 1</span> in the manuscript.</p>\n\n<p class=\"passage_para\">c) Explain ONE way that <span class=\"formatted_text text_decoration:underline\">Image 2</span> illustrates the spread of scientific knowledge in the period before 1450.</p>\n</div>\n</div>\n</div>\n</div>\n","rubricRef":"VR134038_rubric","features":[{"type":"sharedpassage","html":"<p class=\"direction_paragraph\" xmlns=\"http://www.imsglobal.org/xsd/apip/apipv1p0/qtiitem/imsqti_v2p2\" xmlns:xsi=\"http://www.w3.org/2001/XMLSchema-instance\"><i><span class=\"formatted_text text_decoration:underline\">Image 1</span>:</i></p>\n\n<div>\n<div class=\"stimulus_reference\">\n<div class=\"standalone_image\">\n<div class=\"title\">\n<p class=\"title_line passage-title\">ILLUSTRATION SHOWING ASTRONOMERS EMPLOYED BY THE MONGOL ILKHANS OF PERSIA MAKING CALCULATIONS, CHARTING THEIR OBSERVATIONS, AND USING ASTRONOMICAL INSTRUMENTS, EARLY FOURTEENTH CENTURY</p>\n</div>\n<img alt=\"The figure presents an illustration from the early fourteenth century. The illustration shows a group of Muslim astronomers sitting around a tree looking up at the sky while others are writing down measurements and making calculations. In the background, a book and a measuring tool are lying on the ground.\" height=\"228\" src=\"https://assets.learnosity.com/organisations/537/VR134038.g05.png\" width=\"450\" /><span class=\"mandatory_credit_line\"></span>\n\n<p><span class=\"mandatory_credit_line\">Pictures from History/Bridgeman Images</span></p>\n</div>\n\n<div class=\"passage\">\n<div class=\"prose style:1\">\n<p class=\"passage_para\"><span class=\"formatted_text font_style:italic\">The illustration was included in a world history manuscript that was produced for the Mongol court.</span></p>\n</div>\n</div>\n\n<div class=\"passage\">&nbsp;</div>\n\n<div class=\"passage\">&nbsp;</div>\n\n<div class=\"passage\">\n<div class=\"prose style:1\">\n<p class=\"passage_para\"><span class=\"formatted_text text_decoration:underline\">Image 2</span>:</p>\n</div>\n</div>\n\n<div class=\"standalone_image\">\n<div class=\"title\">\n<p class=\"title_line passage-title\">ILLUSTRATION FROM A HEBREW TRANSLATION OF THE <span class=\"formatted_text font_style:italic\">CANON OF MEDICINE</span>, A MUSLIM MEDICAL TEXT. THE TRANSLATION WAS PRODUCED BY A JEWISH SCHOLAR AT THE COURT OF THE CHRISTIAN KINGS OF SICILY, CIRCA 1250</p>\n</div>\n<img alt=\"The figure presents an illustration from the thirteenth century. The illustration is divided into 3 panels. Starting at the top, and moving counterclockwise, the first panel of the illustration shows a room divided into two sections. On the left side a man is leading a horse into the room, while a man and a woman tend to a bedridden person. The right side of the first panel shows a group of 6 people surrounding another bedridden person. The second panel shows Hebrew text. The third panel shows a group of five people surrounding a bed, tending to a bedridden person. One of the people seems to be reading or dictating to the person in bed.\" src=\"https://assets.learnosity.com/organisations/537/VR134038.g07.png\" /><span class=\"mandatory_credit_line\"></span>\n\n<p><span class=\"mandatory_credit_line\">Science History Images / Alamy Stock Photo</span></p>\n</div>\n\n<div class=\"passage\">\n<div class=\"prose style:1\">\n<p class=\"passage_para\"><span class=\"formatted_text font_style:italic\">The illustration shows the various stages of a physicianâ€™s visit with a patient.</span></p>\n</div>\n</div>\n</div>\n</div>\n\n<p class=\"stem_paragraph\">&nbsp;</p>\n"}]}]